The paper focuses on generative modeling of photos using GANs, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of current GANs and proposes techniques to mitigate the problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve manipulating the latent space of GANs, which is related to geometric transformations (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between the breadth of training data distribution and the degree of distributional shift, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
